info.name: HiPipo-Hackathon-Use-Cases
info.description:
#Author: sridevi.miriyala@modusbox.com#

This is the collection to use by the participants attending the Women in Fintech - HiPipo hackathon.
The whole collection is devided into per group and there are 3 groups corresponding to each currencies UGX, ZMW and EUR. Each group has 5 participants, which makes total 15 participants for this hackathon.
The participants are going to check the below usecases:

1. First they will be checking the connectivity to the lab by hitting the request from the connectivity folder. There are 5 requests of this in each group, one request specific to each team.
The team is going to pick the one on their name and run and check all the tests are passing.

2. Once the team is successfully complete the connectivity test, they will be running the p2p interoperatble usecase.
    In this use case, a transfer is being sent from a MSISDN from one DFSP/team from one group to a MSISDN from the other DFSP/team in the same group.
    This is sending money from one person to another person in the same currency, using the MSISDNs.
    Currently the scripts are created for amountType "SEND" and "RECEIVE" on one DFSP name. If the team wants to try rest of the combinations, that will give more handson on the applicaiton.
    But remember, this p2p interoperable case is between the DFSP in teh same group.

    Make sure the tests are all pass before you move on to the next usecase, which is Forex - cross currency usecase.

item.name: payee_initiated_payments
item.description:
#Author: sridevi.miriyala@modusbox.com#
These are called Merchant payments.
These are between the same currency DFSPs, no cross currency is allowed/tested at the moment.
So, a Merchant(BUSINESS_ID) from a DFSP  in Group-0 can send to a MSISDN from another DFSP in Group-0.
